19:23.459 --> 19:25.296
You think we'll see
something tonight?

19:25.296 --> 19:28.704
Well, in order to observe
the universe,

19:28.704 --> 19:31.108
you must put your back
to the future

19:31.108 --> 19:33.846
and fix your eyes on the past.

19:33.846 --> 19:36.986
Such is the way of nature.

19:37.821 --> 19:40.660
Celestial events
that had occurred long ago,

19:40.660 --> 19:42.396
we still see remnants of them.

19:42.396 --> 19:46.271
Hell, we might not know
what happened until

19:46.271 --> 19:48.844
the light travels
across the galaxy

19:48.844 --> 19:51.214
to show us.

19:52.250 --> 19:55.122
But the universe knows.

19:55.122 --> 19:56.391
It always knows.

19:56.391 --> 19:58.429
We are just

19:58.429 --> 20:00.767
echoes of things
that came before.

20:06.344 --> 20:08.750
Look.

20:08.750 --> 20:10.185
It's the Big Dipper.

20:10.185 --> 20:13.225
That's a boat.

20:13.225 --> 20:15.029
A boat?

20:15.029 --> 20:16.799
- I thought it
was supposed to be--
- Nah, white man

20:16.799 --> 20:19.605
calls it the Big Dipper.
It's a boat.

20:19.605 --> 20:22.978
Helps us on our journey
when we go.

20:22.978 --> 20:25.149
Where does it take us to?

20:25.149 --> 20:28.623
Well, they call it
the Milky Way.

20:28.623 --> 20:32.497
But it's a passageway
to the source.

20:32.497 --> 20:35.069
The source that
created everything.

20:35.069 --> 20:37.407
We are just, uh...

20:37.407 --> 20:39.377
energy manifest.

20:39.377 --> 20:41.649
♪<i>♪ You wouldn't know... ♪</i>

20:41.649 --> 20:43.686
Why did they create us?

20:43.686 --> 20:46.291
Well, to prove a point, I guess.

20:47.059 --> 20:49.297
What kind?

20:50.432 --> 20:52.470
That we could still love.

20:52.470 --> 20:55.811
Through it all.
Life's tough.

20:55.811 --> 20:59.283
We should be proud
that we can still love.

21:01.121 --> 21:02.858
Do you still love?

21:04.394 --> 21:06.331
Yeah, I do.

21:07.500 --> 21:10.507
H-How do they know
that you love them?

21:10.507 --> 21:14.080
They-they don't.
They just feel it.

21:14.948 --> 21:18.088
See, y... love doesn't
have to be received,

21:18.088 --> 21:20.460
it can just, uh...

21:20.460 --> 21:22.463
it can just be.

21:22.463 --> 21:25.269
♪<i>♪ The distant horizons ♪</i>

21:25.269 --> 21:27.675
♪<i>♪ Are a glorious sight... ♪</i>

21:27.675 --> 21:29.210
Never seen the stars
this beautiful.

21:29.210 --> 21:30.647
♪<i>♪ And there's getting lost ♪</i>

21:30.647 --> 21:34.755
♪<i>♪ In the Milky Way at night ♪</i>

21:50.687 --> 21:53.893
♪<i>♪ I got a lightning lasso ♪</i>

21:53.893 --> 21:58.201
♪<i>♪ And my trusty horse Blue ♪</i>

21:58.970 --> 22:03.044
♪<i>♪ I've got
a six-shooter too... ♪</i>

22:05.349 --> 22:08.188
♪<i>♪ I have an old Stetson hat... ♪</i>

22:08.188 --> 22:10.293
You like spaghetti soup?

22:10.293 --> 22:11.662
Yeah.

22:11.662 --> 22:13.933
My grandma
used to make that for me.

22:13.933 --> 22:15.970
Yeah? Mine, too.

22:15.970 --> 22:17.406
Huh.

22:17.406 --> 22:19.177
Would you put the water
in the pot, please?

22:19.177 --> 22:20.413
Yeah, of course.

22:20.413 --> 22:23.251
♪<i>♪ Tumbleweed and buffalo ♪</i>

22:23.251 --> 22:26.625
♪<i>♪ The rivers run wild. ♪</i>

22:31.603 --> 22:33.439
How long have you been out here?

22:36.613 --> 22:40.486
On and off
most of my life, I think.

22:40.486 --> 22:42.958
This was my mom's house.

22:42.958 --> 22:46.231
She was from out this way.
My dad was from out your way.

22:46.231 --> 22:48.134
They still around?

22:49.605 --> 22:52.076
Now what the hell do you think?

22:52.076 --> 22:54.681
They died when I was a kid.

22:54.681 --> 22:57.052
Boarding school raised me.

22:58.523 --> 23:00.727
But, mostly, I've...

23:00.727 --> 23:02.797
been on my own ever since.

23:06.404 --> 23:07.974
I'm sorry.

23:08.943 --> 23:10.947
Don't be.

23:13.185 --> 23:14.988
You know...

23:14.988 --> 23:17.727
I don't like people.

23:18.529 --> 23:20.432
But you're all right.

23:21.368 --> 23:25.544
We're, uh,
kindred spirits, I think.

23:25.544 --> 23:27.380
We see things other people can't

23:27.380 --> 23:30.653
and, uh, people are...

23:30.653 --> 23:32.958
either afraid of it

23:32.958 --> 23:34.294
or they're jealous.

23:34.294 --> 23:36.899
Because it's powerful.

23:36.899 --> 23:38.135
So, uh...

23:38.135 --> 23:40.507
stay as long as you like.

23:40.507 --> 23:42.945
We can partner up on our powers,

23:42.945 --> 23:44.715
work the property,

23:44.715 --> 23:46.819
build up the signal.

23:46.819 --> 23:49.891
And get the eggplants ready.

23:49.891 --> 23:51.996
Eh.

23:58.342 --> 24:01.314
This is XM424987.

24:01.314 --> 24:03.318
Anyone receiving?

24:06.659 --> 24:09.631
This is XM424987.

24:09.631 --> 24:12.771
Anyone receiving?

24:17.914 --> 24:20.620
For fuck's sake,
is anybody receiving?

24:29.070 --> 24:30.740
Oh, shit.

24:30.740 --> 24:32.977
Get down, get down!

24:37.554 --> 24:39.825
They're here.

24:40.794 --> 24:42.363
You're gonna have to go.

24:42.363 --> 24:44.535
Who's here-- the Star People?

24:44.535 --> 24:47.073
There... there are no

24:47.073 --> 24:48.576
separate entities.

24:48.576 --> 24:51.949
There's only things
that rely on one another.

24:52.917 --> 24:54.822
Here.

24:54.822 --> 24:56.057
What?

24:59.598 --> 25:00.634
Fuck are the cops doing here?

25:00.634 --> 25:02.102
I-I'll tell them
nothing happened.

25:02.102 --> 25:04.407
- You didn't even touch me.
- Uh, n-n-- Just go home.

25:04.407 --> 25:06.277
Your people probably miss you.

25:07.981 --> 25:10.419
Maximus.

25:10.419 --> 25:12.089
What?

25:12.089 --> 25:13.859
I believe you.

25:15.162 --> 25:16.231
Good.

25:18.936 --> 25:20.807
Hello.

25:24.080 --> 25:25.482
I've been...

25:25.482 --> 25:27.521
I've been waiting for you.

25:27.521 --> 25:29.156
Here, take these.

25:29.156 --> 25:32.229
Come on, Maximus.
We'll take you back.

25:33.398 --> 25:36.338
I forgot to lock the door.

25:36.338 --> 25:37.941
It's okay.

26:31.582 --> 26:34.554
♪<i>♪ Early blue ♪</i>

26:34.554 --> 26:36.525
♪<i>♪ I see you ♪</i>

26:36.525 --> 26:39.063
♪<i>♪ Through my window ♪</i>

26:42.737 --> 26:44.908
♪<i>♪ Becoming lighter ♪</i>

26:44.908 --> 26:46.545
♪<i>♪ As the sun gets brighter ♪</i>

26:46.545 --> 26:49.818
♪<i>♪ And the night goes away ♪</i>

26:52.858 --> 26:55.564
♪<i>♪ I want to close my eyes ♪</i>

26:55.564 --> 26:59.203
♪<i>♪ And pretend
it's night and quiet ♪</i>

26:59.938 --> 27:02.176
♪<i>♪ So peaceful ♪</i>

27:03.613 --> 27:07.119
♪<i>♪ But the rising sun
starts a day to run ♪</i>

27:07.119 --> 27:10.358
♪<i>♪ Wherever it may go ♪</i>

27:14.702 --> 27:17.807
♪<i>♪ Go run away... ♪</i>

27:20.178 --> 27:22.684
Fuck.

27:40.954 --> 27:43.659
Okay, okay, we got this.

27:57.587 --> 28:01.260
Where the fuck are these dead
cats he's talking about?

28:06.772 --> 28:07.741
♪<i>♪ Go run away... ♪</i>

28:07.741 --> 28:10.412
Yes, yes, yes, yes, fuck yes!

28:12.149 --> 28:13.318
Fuck off.

28:16.190 --> 28:18.629
♪<i>♪ In the morning's light ♪</i>

28:18.629 --> 28:22.770
♪<i>♪ I try to hide from people ♪</i>

28:26.645 --> 28:28.816
♪<i>♪ But it's never right ♪</i>

28:28.816 --> 28:33.258
♪<i>♪ I see my friends at night
and it works out fine ♪</i>

28:37.734 --> 28:41.007
♪<i>♪ Go run away ♪</i>

28:43.044 --> 28:46.050
♪<i>♪ Go run away ♪</i>

28:48.021 --> 28:50.893
♪<i>♪ Go run away ♪</i>

28:50.893 --> 28:53.932
♪<i>♪ From my window. ♪</i>
